recordings.rmk: In an area with Abies pinsapo, Quercus rotundifolia, Quercus faginea and Mediterranean scrub, Jays were carrying acorns like crazy. Besides the harsh Jay callings, background of forest ambiance during an unusually warm autumn, with many singing birds and buzzing insects. This sample was recorded right below the crown of Pinsapo de las Escaleretas monument tree, at 1000 m above the sea on Sierra de las Nieves Natural Park (Ronda, S Spain). Sennheiser MKH60 + MKH30 into Shure FP24 preamplifier, PCM M10 recorder. Decoded to Mid-side stereo with free Voxengo VST plugin. You may listen to the uncompressed sample at <http://www.freesound.org/people/dobroide/sounds/328848/>
